value.0: Fashioned in the image of the original itself, and enchanted in kind, this staff was modeled after none other than the famous weapon of choice wielded by an icy, cold-hearted tyrant who sourced her spells both from innate talents and old tomes alike. Among other enhancements, those who wield it will note a subtle imperviousness to the cold, and a barely perceptible vulnerability to fire, much like the initial item's first owner.

A diabolical crossbow; with each pull of the trigger a flaming bolt springs forth, easily burning through the flesh of a foe. Used commonly by assassins, it enchances the wearers sight of hearing and vision, while being sturdy built enough to give it extreme precision and might.

A lanky man who prefers the shadows of Hangman's Cove; word around the street is, he's got some of the best scores in town. Every once in a while he can be seen calling out towards random crowds of adventurers, waiting for one of them to catch his 'drift'.
Useful for carrying water, fruit, liquids, cleaning supplies, or pretty much anything that will fit inside of it, the bucket has been a utilitarian object for many, many years.
A shovel is ideal for moving quantities of dirt from one location to another.  Other uses are possible, of course.

Value.value: Ah, you match the description I've been given. This is the item in question. I'm told there's a marked shipment in West Southport's warehouse for you to, ah, "do your thing."
